1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
This is Surokkha AI — an AI safety app for women in Bangladesh.

2
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:28,000
Paste any suspicious message — it tells you if it's a scam, and why.

3
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:34,000
First example — a bKash fraud message, written in Banglish.

4
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:48,000
A red alert — 99% risk. It explains: asks for OTP, threatens to block the account.

5
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Now a romance / marriage scam — fully in Bangla.

6
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:12,000
Another alert. It catches the fast marriage proposal, the "abroad" promise, and the money request — exactly how real scams work.

7
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:20,000
But it doesn't cry wolf. Let's try an ordinary message.

8
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Green — safe. No false alarm. That trust is what keeps people using it.

9
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:42,000
Your own text works too — here, a grooming attempt in Banglish.

10
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:54,000
Caught it — pressure to keep secrets and move to a private app.

11
00:01:54,000 --> 00:02:14,000
It works in 3 layers — fast rules, an AI model that reads Bangla, Banglish and English, and a layer that explains the reason.

12
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Your messages are never stored. Next, the model runs fully on-device — completely private.

13
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:45,000
Truecaller catches spam calls — Surokkha AI catches dangerous conversations. Thank you.
